Summary : This bar chart presents the monthly gas usage history, measured in total therms used, over a one-year period from August of one year to August of the next.

bar chart:
# Title & Axes :
  • Title: "Gas Usage History (Total therms used)"
  • Y-axis: "Therms" (vertical), with tick marks at 0, 5, 10, 15, and 20.
  • X-axis: Months from "AUG" (year 1) through "AUG" (year 2).

# Data Points :
  • Each bar represents total therms used for a given month.
  • Approximate values (from visual estimation):
    – AUG (year 1): ~6 therms
    – SEP: ~7 therms
    – OCT: ~8 therms
    – NOV: ~9 therms
    – DEC: ~10 therms
    – JAN: ~13 therms
    – FEB: ~12 therms
    – MAR: ~11 therms
    – APR: ~10 therms
    – MAY: ~9 therms
    – JUN: ~8 therms
    – JUL: ~7 therms
    – AUG (year 2): ~7 therms

# Design Encodings :
  • Bars are light blue.
  • No gridlines except for major Y-axis ticks.
  • No error bars or additional series.

# Distribution & Trends :
  • Usage increases from August through January, peaking in January.
  • Gradual decline from February through July.
  • Lowest usage in August and September; highest in January.

# Analysis :
  • Gas usage is highest during winter months (December–February), peaking in January, and lowest during summer months (August–September).
  • The pattern suggests seasonal variation, likely due to heating needs in colder months.
  • No outliers or abrupt changes; the trend is smooth and consistent across the year.

Summary : This figure presents a monthly history of electric usage (in kWh) broken down by On-Peak, Off-Peak, and Super Off-Peak periods, along with key usage statistics for the most recent billing cycle.

# Title & Axes :
  • Title: "Electric Usage History (Total kWh used)"
  • Y-axis: "Kilowatt Hours" (range: 0 to 245, with tick marks at 49, 98, 147, 196, 245)
  • X-axis: Months (labels: AUG, SEP, OCT, NOV, DEC, JAN, FEB, MAR, APR, MAY, JUN, JUL; years indicated as 19 and 20)

# Data Points :
  • Three series per month:
    – On-Peak (orange bars)
    – Off-Peak (blue bars)
    – Super Off-Peak (yellow bars)
  • Each month shows stacked bars for each usage type; exact values not specified but visually estimated.

# Design Encodings :

  • Stacked bar format for each month.
  • Legend provided for colour coding.

# Usage Statistics :
  • Total kWh used in billing cycle: 143
  • Daily average kWh: 4.8
  • Daily average kWh last month: 3.6
  • Change in daily avg kWh from last year: 54.8% increase
  • Change in daily avg kWh from last month: 33.3% increase
  • Max monthly demand: 1.0
  • Max annual demand: 1.0
  • Days in billing cycle: 30

# Analysis :
  • Electric usage peaks in January and February, with the highest total kWh in these months.
  • Off-Peak usage (blue) is the largest contributor in peak months.
  • Usage drops in spring and rises again in summer.
  • The most recent billing cycle shows a significant increase in daily average kWh compared to both last month and last year.
  • Demand values remain constant at 1.0 for both monthly and annual maximums.
  • The data suggests seasonal variation, with winter months showing higher consumption.
